  "Motorcycle tycoon Rahul Bajaj's nephew Anurang Jain started Endurance Technologies in 1985 to supply aluminum castings to his uncle's Bajaj Auto.\r\n",
  "Jain owns 58% of Endurance, which supplies parts for two-wheelers and three-wheelers in India and car parts in Europe.",
  "Endurance has 18 factories in India and 8 in Europe.",
  "The company's shares have soared since its listing in 2016."
